===Noun===
''pidgin''

# ''(language)'' an [[amalgamation]] of two [[disparate]] [[language]]s, used between the two [[population]]s as a ''[[lingua franca]]''; lacks [[formalize]]d [[grammar]] and has small, [[utilitarian]] [[vocabulary]] as well as having no native speakers.
#* [[Middle English]] likely began as a '''pidgin''' between the [[Norman]] invaders and the Anglo-Saxon-speaking ([[Old English]]) occupants of [[Britain]]. Otherwise, how could they have gotten any business done?

